Algorithm:
1. Initialize two variables, maxElement and minElement, to hold the maximum and minimum values.
2. Set maxElement to the first element of the array and minElement to the first element.
3. Loop through the array:
* If the current element is greater than maxElement, update maxElement.
* If the current element is smaller than minElement, update minElement.
4. After the loop, maxElement will hold the maximum value and minElement will hold the minimum value.
